---
import ProjectLayout from '../../layouts/ProjectLayout.astro'
---

<ProjectLayout
  badge="IEEE Research · CASE 2026 · Accepted"
  title="High-Speed Fault Detection — 126× Faster than the Baseline."
  description="A hybrid CNN-PCA pipeline that achieves 126× speedup in bearing fault detection while maintaining 99.1% accuracy — accepted to IEEE CASE 2026 (Automation Science & Engineering)."
  coverImage="/portfolio/images/case_cover.webp"
  coverAlt="High-speed fault detection CNN-PCA pipeline visualization"
  ogImage="https://alesso-24.github.io/portfolio/images/case_cover.webp"
  meta={[
    { label: 'Venue',    value: 'IEEE CASE 2026 — Automation Science' },
    { label: 'Status',   value: '✓ Accepted · IEEE Xplore ~Nov 2026' },
    { label: 'Speedup',  value: '126× vs. baseline' },
    { label: 'Accuracy', value: '99.1% on CWRU benchmark' },
    { label: 'Role',     value: 'Lead Researcher & System Architect' },
  ]}
>

  <!-- IEEE badge -->
  <div data-reveal style="margin: clamp(20px,3vh,32px) 0 0; display:flex; align-items:center; gap:16px; flex-wrap:wrap;">
    <div style="
      display:inline-flex; align-items:center; gap:10px;
      padding:12px 24px; border-radius:100px;
      background:rgba(37,64,192,0.08); border: 1px solid rgba(37,64,192,0.2);
    ">
      <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="#2540c0" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M12 2L2 7l10 5 10-5-10-5zM2 17l10 5 10-5M2 12l10 5 10-5"/></svg>
      <span style="font:700 12px 'Hanken Grotesk',system-ui,sans-serif; letter-spacing:0.12em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#2540c0;">
        IEEE Xplore · Expected November 2026
      </span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="divider" />

  <!-- Pull quote -->
  <blockquote class="pull-quote" data-reveal>
    <p>"126× faster isn't an optimization — it's a qualitative shift. What was too slow for real-time use suddenly becomes the fastest thing in the room."</p>
  </blockquote>

  <hr class="divider" />

  <h2 class="section-h2" data-reveal>The Speed Problem in Fault Detection.</h2>

  <p class="prose" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="60">
    Bearing fault detection in industrial environments is computationally demanding.
    Traditional deep-learning approaches achieve high accuracy but require inference
    times that are incompatible with real-time control loops — especially for
    high-speed machinery running at thousands of RPM where fault progression
    can happen within seconds.
  </p>
  <p class="prose" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="100">
    This research introduces a hybrid CNN-PCA architecture that front-loads dimensionality
    reduction via PCA (eliminating ~87% of redundant features before the CNN sees the data),
    enabling the classifier to run 126× faster than a comparable full-feature CNN baseline
    while retaining 99.1% accuracy on the CWRU benchmark dataset.
  </p>

  <!-- 126x stat headline -->
  <div data-reveal data-reveal-delay="140" style="
    text-align:center; padding: clamp(32px,5vh,64px) 0;
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(33,31,26,0.1); border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(33,31,26,0.1);
    margin: clamp(28px,4vh,48px) 0;
  ">
    <div style="font-family:'Instrument Serif',serif; font-size:clamp(72px,14vw,160px); line-height:0.9;
                color:#ea6a2e; letter-spacing:-0.04em; font-weight:400;">
      126×
    </div>
    <p style="margin:16px 0 0; font:600 13px 'Hanken Grotesk',system-ui,sans-serif;
              letter-spacing:0.12em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#6f6a5f;">
      Faster than full-feature CNN baseline
    </p>
  </div>

  <hr class="divider" />

  <h2 class="section-h2" data-reveal>The CNN-PCA Architecture.</h2>

  <p class="prose" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="60">
    The key insight: not all dimensions of a vibration signal are equally informative
    for fault classification. PCA identifies the principal components that account for
    95% of variance — and discards the rest before the CNN ever processes the data.
    The CNN then operates on a dramatically smaller, more expressive feature space.
  </p>

  <div class="tech-grid" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="100">
    <div class="tech-card">
      <div class="tech-num">01</div>
      <h3>PCA Pre-Processing</h3>
      <p>Principal component analysis reduces input dimensionality from ~1500 to ~190 features
      per sample — removing noise while preserving the fault-relevant signal structure.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="tech-card">
      <div class="tech-num">02</div>
      <h3>Lightweight CNN</h3>
      <p>A shallow 3-layer 1D CNN trained on PCA-compressed inputs achieves 99.1% accuracy —
      without the computational overhead of processing raw high-dimensional vibration data.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="tech-card">
      <div class="tech-num">03</div>
      <h3>FPU Bug Discovery</h3>
      <p>During hardware testing, an undocumented FPU edge case was discovered in the target
      microcontroller — leading to a novel software workaround now included in the paper
      as a deployment contribution.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Figures -->
  <div data-reveal style="border-radius:18px; overflow:hidden; margin: clamp(28px,4vh,48px) 0; box-shadow: 0 22px 50px -24px rgba(37,64,192,0.35);">
    <img src="/portfolio/images/case_fdr.webp" alt="CNN-PCA fault detection pipeline diagram"
         loading="lazy" decoding="async" style="width:100%; height:auto; display:block;" />
  </div>

  <div data-reveal style="display:grid; grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr; gap:clamp(12px,2vw,24px); margin-bottom: clamp(28px,4vh,48px);">
    <div style="border-radius:14px; overflow:hidden; box-shadow:0 18px 44px -20px rgba(37,64,192,0.3);">
      <img src="/portfolio/images/case_latency.webp" alt="Latency comparison showing 126× speedup"
           loading="lazy" decoding="async" style="width:100%; height:auto; display:block;" />
    </div>
    <div style="border-radius:14px; overflow:hidden; box-shadow:0 18px 44px -20px rgba(234,106,46,0.3);">
      <img src="/portfolio/images/case_pca.webp" alt="PCA feature space visualization"
           loading="lazy" decoding="async" style="width:100%; height:auto; display:block;" />
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="callout" data-reveal>
    <strong>On the FPU Bug.</strong>
    During deployment testing, we encountered consistent numerical errors in the PCA
    matrix multiplication on the target hardware. After systematic debugging, we traced
    it to a denormalized-float edge case in the hardware FPU — undocumented for this
    chip variant. The software workaround adds ~3μs per inference and is now part of the paper.
  </div>

</ProjectLayout>

<style>
  .pull-quote {
    border-left: 3px solid #ea6a2e;
    margin: clamp(32px,5vh,56px) 0;
    padding: clamp(16px,2.5vw,24px) clamp(20px,3vw,32px);
    background: #efe7d8;
    border-radius: 0 12px 12px 0;
  }
  .pull-quote p {
    margin: 0; font-family: 'Instrument Serif', serif;
    font-size: clamp(17px, 1.9vw, 24px); line-height: 1.4;
    color: #211f1a; font-style: italic;
  }
  .tech-num {
    font-family: 'Instrument Serif', serif; font-size: 32px;
    color: #ea6a2e; line-height: 1; margin-bottom: 12px; letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }
</style>
